---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Button from '../../components/Button.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Redesigning Complex Science for Millions"
  description="Case study: Redesigning an interactive biochemical pathways platform for a major pharmaceutical company, improving usability for millions of users worldwide."
>
  <!-- Hero - Full Width -->
  <section class="relative">
    <!-- Back button -->
    <div class="px-6 md:px-20 py-8">
      <a href="/#work" class="inline-flex items-center text-body text-text-secondary hover:text-accent transition-colors">
        <svg class="w-5 h-5 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7" />
        </svg>
        Back to Work
      </a>
    </div>

    <!-- Hero Content -->
    <div class="px-6 md:px-20 pb-16 md:pb-24">
      <div class="max-w-4xl">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 mb-6">
          <span class="px-4 py-2 bg-accent/10 text-accent rounded-full text-body-sm font-medium">UX/UI Design</span>
          <span class="px-4 py-2 bg-secondary text-text-secondary rounded-full text-body-sm">2023</span>
          <span class="px-4 py-2 bg-secondary text-text-secondary rounded-full text-body-sm">Major Pharmaceutical Company</span>
        </div>

        <h1 class="text-h1-mobile md:text-h1 font-serif font-bold text-text-primary mb-6 leading-tight">
          Redesigning Complex Science for Millions
        </h1>

        <p class="text-body-lg text-text-secondary leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
          Redesigned an interactive biochemical pathways platform used by millions of researchers worldwide, improving usability while maintaining rich scientific content.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Hero Image - Full Width -->
    <div class="w-full">
      <img
        src="/images/projects/pharma/deliverables/Context.png"
        alt="Biochemical Pathways Platform"
        class="w-full h-auto"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Overview - 3 Columns -->
  <section class="px-6 md:px-20 py-20 md:py-32">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-12">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-h4 font-semibold text-text-primary mb-4">The Challenge</h3>
            <p class="text-body text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
              A biochemical pathways platform serves millions of researchers, educators, and students worldwide.
              The website needed a redesign to align with current branding standards while preserving complex
              interactive features and scientific accuracy.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-h4 font-semibold text-text-primary mb-4">My Role</h3>
            <p class="text-body text-text-secondary mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              Concept Design, Interface Design, Visual Design, Usability Testing
            </p>
            <p class="text-body-sm text-text-secondary">
              <span class="font-medium text-text-primary">Team:</span> UX Research, Program Management
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-h4 font-semibold text-text-primary mb-4">The Outcome</h3>
            <p class="text-body text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
              Complete platform redesign with responsive design for seamless usability across all devices.
              Mobile-first approach addressed critical usability gaps while maintaining scientific depth.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Project Overview - Full Width with Background -->
  <section class="py-20 md:py-32 bg-secondary/30">
    <div class="px-6 md:px-20">
      <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
        <p class="text-body-lg text-text-primary leading-relaxed mb-12 max-w-3xl">
          The existing platform was functional but outdated, with significant usability issues on mobile devices and inconsistencies with the client's current brand identity.
        </p>

        <img
          src="/images/projects/pharma/deliverables/Project overview.png"
          alt="Pharma Project Overview"
          class="w-full rounded-2xl shadow-large"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Context Section -->
  <section class="px-6 md:px-20 py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-h2-mobile md:text-h3 font-serif font-bold text-text-primary mb-8">Context</h2>

        <div class="mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-h3 font-semibold text-text-primary mb-6">A Platform for Advanced Biochemical Insight</h3>
          <p class="text-body-lg text-text-primary leading-relaxed mb-6">
            The Biochemical Pathways maps provide an interactive overview of cell chemical reactions across different species and organs. With a user base of millions worldwide spanning academia, research institutions, and pharmaceutical companies, the platform serves as an essential resource for understanding complex biological systems.
          </p>
          <div class="border-l-2 border-text-primary px-6 py-4 mt-6">
            <p class="text-body font-semibold text-text-primary">
              The Challenge: Transform an outdated but mission-critical interface while maintaining scientific rigor and complex interactive functionality.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Research & Discovery Section -->
      <section class="mb-20">
        <h2 class="text-h2-mobile md:text-h3 font-bold text-text-primary mb-8">Research & Discovery</h2>

        <h3 class="text-h3-mobile md:text-h4 font-semibold text-text-primary mb-6">Understanding Users Through Direct Feedback</h3>
        <p class="text-body-lg text-text-primary leading-relaxed mb-8">
          Following stakeholder interviews and comprehensive user research conducted by the team, I participated in <strong>5 usability tests</strong> to identify pain points in our redesign concepts.
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-10">
          <!-- Key Findings -->
          <div>
            <h4 class="text-h4 font-semibold text-text-primary mb-6">Key Findings</h4>

            <div class="space-y-6">
              <div class="border-l-2 border-text-tertiary bg-secondary px-6 py-5">
                <h5 class="text-body font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">Mobile Experience Was Broken</h5>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-body text-text-secondary">
                  <li>"Using the map on the smartphone is difficult"</li>
                  <li>Mobile navigation was particularly challenging for complex pathway exploration</li>
                  <li>Zoom level controls were unintuitive</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="border-l-2 border-text-tertiary bg-secondary px-6 py-5">
                <h5 class="text-body font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">Desktop Had Its Own Issues</h5>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-body text-text-secondary">
                  <li>"The overall menu/start was confusing"</li>
                  <li>Users struggled to find the second map</li>
                  <li>Toggle functionality under "Filter" didn't meet expectations</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="border-l-2 border-text-tertiary bg-secondary px-6 py-5">
                <h5 class="text-body font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">What Users Valued</h5>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-body text-text-secondary">
                  <li>"Virtual should provide the same overview as the printed version"</li>
                  <li>"Overview and connectivity of cycles is great"</li>
                  <li>"Highlighting and labeling of area overlays is a strength"</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="border-l-2 border-text-primary px-8 py-6 mt-8 mb-8">
            <p class="text-body-lg text-text-primary leading-relaxed">
              These insights revealed that users needed quick access to comparison features, brand consistency for credibility, and a careful balance between information density and readability.
            </p>
          </div>

          <a href="/images/projects/pharma/deliverables/Usability testing.png" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="block group cursor-zoom-in">
            <img
              src="/images/projects/pharma/deliverables/Usability testing.png"
              alt="Usability Testing Insights"
              class="w-full rounded shadow-soft transition-all duration-300 group-hover:shadow-medium group-hover:scale-[1.02]"
            />
            <p class="text-caption text-text-tertiary text-center mt-4 group-hover:text-accent transition-colors duration-300">Click to enlarge</p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Design Approach Section -->
      <section class="mb-20">
        <h2 class="text-h2-mobile md:text-h3 font-bold text-text-primary mb-8">Design Approach</h2>

        <div class="mb-10">
          <h3 class="text-h3-mobile md:text-h4 font-semibold text-text-primary mb-6">Mobile-First, User-Centered Design</h3>
          <p class="text-body-lg text-text-primary leading-relaxed mb-6">
            We prioritized the mobile experience, knowing that many users access the platform on various devices in lab settings. User feedback guided our selection of existing design system components and the development of new ones to address specific usability challenges.
          </p>
          <div class="border-l-2 border-text-primary px-6 py-4">
            <p class="text-body font-semibold text-text-primary">
              The Guiding Principle: Balance aesthetic appeal with scientific rigor - create a clean, uncluttered interface that doesn't compromise on the depth of information users need.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
          <h3 class="text-h3-mobile md:text-h4 font-semibold text-text-primary mb-6">Working Within the Design System</h3>
          <p class="text-body-lg text-text-primary leading-relaxed mb-4">
            We leveraged the client's existing design system components while developing new ones as needed. This approach ensured:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-3 mb-6">
            <li class="text-body text-text-primary flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3 mt-1.5 text-accent font-bold">→</span>
              <span><strong>Brand consistency</strong> across the company's digital products</span>
            </li>
            <li class="text-body text-text-primary flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3 mt-1.5 text-accent font-bold">→</span>
              <span><strong>Faster development</strong> through reusable components</span>
            </li>
            <li class="text-body text-text-primary flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3 mt-1.5 text-accent font-bold">→</span>
              <span><strong>Professional polish</strong> that builds user trust</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-body text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-8">
            We documented comprehensive specifications covering user flows, component behavior, and functionality details - critical for a platform this complex.
          </p>

          <img
            src="/images/projects/pharma/deliverables/Process.png"
            alt="Design Process Overview"
            class="w-full rounded shadow-soft"
          />
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Key Design Decisions Section -->
      <section class="mb-20">
        <h2 class="text-h2-mobile md:text-h3 font-bold text-text-primary mb-8">Key Design Decisions</h2>

        <div class="space-y-12">
          <!-- Decision 1 -->
          <div class="border-b border-border pb-8">
            <h3 class="text-h3-mobile md:text-h4 font-semibold text-text-primary mb-4">1. Mobile-First Navigation Redesign</h3>

            <div class="mb-6">
              <p class="text-body-sm font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">The Problem:</p>
              <p class="text-body text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
                The existing navigation was overwhelming on small screens, making pathway exploration frustrating.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <p class="text-body-sm font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">The Solution:</p>
              <p class="text-body text-text-primary leading-relaxed mb-4">
                We created a streamlined bottom navigation with clear hierarchy:
              </p>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-body text-text-secondary">
                <li>Overview → Focus → Filter flow that guides users naturally</li>
                <li>Large, thumb-friendly touch targets (minimum 44x44px)</li>
                <li>Collapsible panels to maximize map viewing space</li>
                <li>Clear visual indicators for active states</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Decision 2 -->
          <div class="border-b border-border pb-8">
            <h3 class="text-h3-mobile md:text-h4 font-semibold text-text-primary mb-4">2. Improved Search & Filter Experience</h3>

            <div class="mb-6">
              <p class="text-body-sm font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">The Problem:</p>
              <p class="text-body text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
                Users couldn't find specific pathways efficiently, especially on mobile.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <p class="text-body-sm font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">The Solution:</p>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-body text-text-secondary">
                <li>Prominent search bar with autocomplete</li>
                <li>Redesigned filter system with clear categories (Enzymes, Substrates/Products, Compounds)</li>
                <li>Search results with context ("Show 114 matches in Cellular and Molecular Processes")</li>
                <li>Legend panel for understanding map notation</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Decision 3 -->
          <div class="border-b border-border pb-8">
            <h3 class="text-h3-mobile md:text-h4 font-semibold text-text-primary mb-4">3. Enhanced Focus & Overlay Tools</h3>

            <div class="mb-6">
              <p class="text-body-sm font-semibold text-text-primary mb-2">The Problem:</p>
              <p class="text-body text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
                Users valued the ability to focus on specific pathways but found the controls confusing.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <p class="text-body-sm font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">The Solution:</p>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-body text-text-secondary">
                <li>Focus tooltip with clear descriptions of pathway functions</li>
                <li>Overlay cards for detailed vs. schematic views</li>
                <li>Drawing tools for annotations (future enhancement)</li>
                <li>Information architecture that reveals complexity progressively</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Solution Section -->
      <section class="mb-20">
        <h2 class="text-h2-mobile md:text-h3 font-bold text-text-primary mb-8">Solution</h2>

        <div class="space-y-12">
          <!-- Desktop Experience -->
          <div class="pb-8 border-b border-border">
            <h3 class="text-h3-mobile md:text-h4 font-semibold text-text-primary mb-6">Desktop Experience</h3>
            <p class="text-body-lg text-text-primary leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Our design balances aesthetics and usability. We strove for simple and clear navigation, knowing it improves user engagement.
            </p>

            <h4 class="text-body font-semibold text-text-primary mb-4">Key Features:</h4>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-body text-text-secondary mb-8">
              <li>Tab-based navigation (Metabolic Pathways / Cellular and Molecular Processes)</li>
              <li>Persistent search and filter controls</li>
              <li>Overview, Focus, and Filter modes accessible at all times</li>
              <li>Clean visual hierarchy that guides users through dense scientific content</li>
              <li>Zoom controls optimized for precision work</li>
            </ul>

            <a href="/images/projects/pharma/deliverables/Desktop final design.png" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="block group cursor-zoom-in">
              <img
                src="/images/projects/pharma/deliverables/Desktop final design.png"
                alt="Desktop Final Design"
                class="w-full rounded-lg shadow-soft transition-all duration-300 group-hover:shadow-medium group-hover:scale-[1.02]"
              />
              <p class="text-caption text-text-tertiary text-center mt-4 group-hover:text-accent transition-colors duration-300">Click to enlarge</p>
            </a>
          </div>

          <!-- Mobile Experience -->
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-h3-mobile md:text-h4 font-semibold text-text-primary mb-6">Mobile Experience</h3>
            <p class="text-body-lg text-text-primary leading-relaxed mb-8">
              We delivered a mobile-first design that provides an intuitive user experience for exploring complex pathways:
            </p>

            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-body font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">Homepage</h4>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-body-sm text-text-secondary">
                  <li>Clear entry point with pathway selection</li>
                  <li>Simplified menu structure</li>
                  <li>Quick access to frequently used features</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div>
                <h4 class="text-body font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">Onboarding</h4>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-body-sm text-text-secondary">
                  <li>First-time user guidance</li>
                  <li>"Skip Guide" option for returning users</li>
                  <li>Contextual tooltips explaining new features</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div>
                <h4 class="text-body font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">Map Interaction</h4>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-body-sm text-text-secondary">
                  <li>Optimized pinch-to-zoom</li>
                  <li>Bottom sheet navigation for easy thumb reach</li>
                  <li>Full-screen map mode</li>
                  <li>Smooth transitions between views</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-8 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <a href="/images/projects/pharma/deliverables/Mobile design final -1.png" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="block group cursor-zoom-in">
                <img
                  src="/images/projects/pharma/deliverables/Mobile design final -1.png"
                  alt="Mobile Design - Overview"
                  class="w-full rounded shadow-soft transition-all duration-300 group-hover:shadow-medium group-hover:scale-[1.02]"
                />
                <p class="text-caption text-text-tertiary text-center mt-4 group-hover:text-accent transition-colors duration-300">Click to enlarge</p>
              </a>
              <a href="/images/projects/pharma/deliverables/Mobile2.png" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="block group cursor-zoom-in">
                <img
                  src="/images/projects/pharma/deliverables/Mobile2.png"
                  alt="Mobile Design - Focus Mode"
                  class="w-full rounded shadow-soft transition-all duration-300 group-hover:shadow-medium group-hover:scale-[1.02]"
                />
                <p class="text-caption text-text-tertiary text-center mt-4 group-hover:text-accent transition-colors duration-300">Click to enlarge</p>
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Implementation Section -->
      <section class="mb-20">
        <h2 class="text-h2-mobile md:text-h3 font-bold text-text-primary mb-8">Implementation & Handover</h2>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-h3-mobile md:text-h4 font-semibold text-text-primary mb-6">Ensuring Seamless Development</h3>
          <p class="text-body-lg text-text-primary leading-relaxed mb-6">
            We documented comprehensive specifications covering:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-3 mb-8 text-body text-text-secondary">
            <li>User flows for all primary and secondary tasks</li>
            <li>Component behavior and states</li>
            <li>Interactive feature requirements</li>
            <li>Responsive breakpoints and adaptations</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-body text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-6">
            These specifications were thoroughly explained in the final meeting with the client's development team to ensure accurate implementation.
          </p>
          <div class="border-l-2 border-text-primary px-6 py-4 mb-8">
            <p class="text-body font-semibold text-text-primary">
              Legacy Impact: The design system components we developed have been integrated into the client's broader design system for use in future projects.
            </p>
          </div>

          <a href="/images/projects/pharma/deliverables/DesignSystem.png" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="block group cursor-zoom-in mb-6">
            <img
              src="/images/projects/pharma/deliverables/DesignSystem.png"
              alt="Design System Components"
              class="w-full rounded shadow-soft transition-all duration-300 group-hover:shadow-medium group-hover:scale-[1.02]"
            />
            <p class="text-caption text-text-tertiary text-center mt-4 group-hover:text-accent transition-colors duration-300">Click to enlarge</p>
          </a>

          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
            <a href="/images/projects/pharma/deliverables/DS - Sidebar.png" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="block group cursor-zoom-in">
              <img
                src="/images/projects/pharma/deliverables/DS - Sidebar.png"
                alt="Design System - Sidebar Component"
                class="w-full rounded shadow-soft transition-all duration-300 group-hover:shadow-medium group-hover:scale-[1.02]"
              />
              <p class="text-caption text-text-tertiary text-center mt-4 group-hover:text-accent transition-colors duration-300">Click to enlarge</p>
            </a>
            <a href="/images/projects/pharma/deliverables/DS - Accordion.png" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="block group cursor-zoom-in">
              <img
                src="/images/projects/pharma/deliverables/DS - Accordion.png"
                alt="Design System - Accordion Component"
                class="w-full rounded shadow-soft transition-all duration-300 group-hover:shadow-medium group-hover:scale-[1.02]"
              />
              <p class="text-caption text-text-tertiary text-center mt-4 group-hover:text-accent transition-colors duration-300">Click to enlarge</p>
            </a>
            <a href="/images/projects/pharma/deliverables/DS - Overlay.png" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="block group cursor-zoom-in">
              <img
                src="/images/projects/pharma/deliverables/DS - Overlay.png"
                alt="Design System - Overlay Component"
                class="w-full rounded shadow-soft transition-all duration-300 group-hover:shadow-medium group-hover:scale-[1.02]"
              />
              <p class="text-caption text-text-tertiary text-center mt-4 group-hover:text-accent transition-colors duration-300">Click to enlarge</p>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Impact & Reflections Section -->
      <section class="mb-20">
        <h2 class="text-h2-mobile md:text-h3 font-bold text-text-primary mb-8">Impact & Reflections</h2>

        <div class="space-y-10">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-h3-mobile md:text-h4 font-semibold text-text-primary mb-6">What I Took Away</h3>

            <div class="space-y-6">
              <div class="border-l-2 border-text-tertiary px-8 py-6">
                <h4 class="text-body font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">1. Balancing Domain Expertise with Usability</h4>
                <p class="text-body text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
                  Scientific accuracy couldn't be compromised for simplicity. The key was making complexity manageable, not hiding it. This taught me to deeply understand user needs within highly specialized domains.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="border-l-2 border-text-tertiary px-8 py-6">
                <h4 class="text-body font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">2. Mobile-First Is Essential, Even for "Professional" Platforms</h4>
                <p class="text-body text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
                  Initial assumptions suggested desktop would be primary, but research showed mobile usage was critical. This reinforced the importance of data-driven design decisions over assumptions.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="border-l-2 border-text-tertiary px-8 py-6">
                <h4 class="text-body font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">3. Design Systems Enable Creativity Within Constraints</h4>
                <p class="text-body text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
                  Working within an existing design system didn't limit creativity - it provided a foundation for solving new problems efficiently while ensuring consistency.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="border-l-2 border-text-tertiary px-8 py-6">
                <h4 class="text-body font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">4. Documentation Is As Important As Design</h4>
                <p class="text-body text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
                  For complex interactive features, thorough documentation and developer collaboration were critical. Beautiful designs fail if they can't be implemented accurately.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Measurable Outcomes -->
          <div class="pt-8 border-t border-border">
            <h3 class="text-h3-mobile md:text-h4 font-semibold text-text-primary mb-6">Measurable Outcomes</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-body text-text-secondary mb-8">
              <li>Responsive design optimized for mobile, tablet, and desktop</li>
              <li>Improved usability validated through testing</li>
              <li>Brand alignment with client's design system</li>
              <li>Scalable components integrated into company-wide design system</li>
              <li>Millions of users worldwide benefit from improved accessibility</li>
            </ul>

            <img
              src="/images/projects/pharma/deliverables/Learnings.png"
              alt="Key Learnings"
              class="w-full rounded shadow-soft"
            />
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Closing Statement -->
        <div class="mt-12 text-center">
          <p class="text-body-lg text-text-secondary italic leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mx-auto">
            This project demonstrates my ability to tackle complex, data-rich interfaces while maintaining focus on user needs. The platform continues to serve the global scientific community, balancing cutting-edge functionality with intuitive design.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>

  <!-- Back to Work CTA -->
  <section class="px-6 md:px-20 pb-3xl">
    <div class="max-w-readable mx-auto text-center border-t border-border pt-xl">
      <Button href="/#work" variant="secondary" size="large">
        ← Back to All Work
      </Button>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
